   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,764:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |            | Infrastructure Modification|              |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,765:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |            | Specification & Monitoring |              |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,766:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |            | Threshold Generation       |              |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,767:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |            +----------------------------+              |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,768:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |                                                       |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,769:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: +-------------------------------------------------------+
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,769:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.2 Graph-Based Topology Model
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,770:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The infrastructure topology is represented as a directed graph G = (V, E) where:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,771:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,772:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: V (Vertices):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,774:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Each vertex represents an infrastructure component with the following typed
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,775:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: attributes:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,775:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,776:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: type
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,777:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : One of {load
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,778:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,778:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: balancer, web
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,779:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,780:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: server, app
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,780:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,782:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: server, database, cache, queue,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,782:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: storage, dns, external
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,783:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,784:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: api, ai
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,784:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,785:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: agent, llm
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,785:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,786:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: endpoint, tool
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,786:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,787:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: service, agent
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,788:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,788:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: orchestrator,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,789:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: custom}
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,790:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,790:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: replicas
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,791:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Integer replica count for parallel redundancy modeling
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,792:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,792:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: metrics
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,796:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Current resource utilization (CPU%, memory%, disk%, network
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,796:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: connections, open files)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,797:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,798:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: capacity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,800:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Resource limits (max connections, max RPS, connection pool size,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,801:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: timeout, retry multiplier)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,801:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,802:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: network
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Network characteristics (RTT, packet loss rate, jitter, DNS resolution
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: time, TLS handshake time)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: runtime_jitter
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,808:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Application-level jitter sources (GC pause duration/frequency,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: scheduling jitter)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,811:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: operational_profile
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,812:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : MTBF (hours), MTTR (minutes), deploy downtime
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,813:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (seconds)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,813:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: autoscaling
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : HPA/KEDA configuration (min/max replicas, thresholds, delays,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,816:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: step size)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,817:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,818:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: failover
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Failover configuration (enabled, promotion time, health check interval,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: threshold)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,821:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,822:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: circuit_breaker
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,823:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Circuit breaker configuration (enabled, threshold, reset
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,824:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: timeout)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,824:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,825:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: external_sla
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,826:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Provider SLA percentage for external dependencies
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,827:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,828:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: team
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,829:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Operational team readiness (runbook coverage %, automation %)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,829:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,830:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: E (Edges):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,832:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Each directed edge (u, v) represents that component u depends on component v, with
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,832:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: attributes:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,833:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,834:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: dependency_type
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,835:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : One of {requires, optional, async}
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,836:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,836:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: weight
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,837:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Dependency strength (0.0 to 1.0)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,838:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,839:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: latency_ms
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,839:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Expected edge latency
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,840:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,841:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: circuit_breaker
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,842:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Edge-level circuit breaker configuration
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,843:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,843:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: retry_strategy
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,845:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Retry configuration (enabled, max retries, backoff strategy)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,845:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,846:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: singleflight
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,847:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Request coalescing configuration
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,860:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The topology may be defined via a declarative YAML schema, import from Terraform state files, import from cloud
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,864:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: provider APIs (AWS, GCP, Azure), import from Prometheus/monitoring metrics, import from Kubernetes cluster
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,865:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: state, or an interactive step-by-step wizard.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,866:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.3 Automated Fault Scenario Generation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,868:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The scenario generator produces fault scenarios across 30 categories, including but not limited to:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,868:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,870:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Single-component DOWN for each component in V
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,870:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,871:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Traffic spike scenarios at multipliers {1.5x, 2x, 3x, 5x, 10x}
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,873:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Pairwise combination failures: C(|V|, 2)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Triple combination failures: C(|V|, 3)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  5 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,879:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Component-type-specific faults (database replication lag, cache stampede, queue backpressure, DNS
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,879:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: failure, external API timeout, etc.)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  6 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Network partition scenarios (zone isolation, cross-zone partition)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,882:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  7 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,883:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Gradual degradation scenarios (resource leak, configuration drift)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,883:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  8 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,889:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: AI agent-specific scenarios (LLM endpoint rate limiting, tool service unavailability, context
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,891:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: overflow under high-concurrency orchestration, coordinated grounding source failures)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,892:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.4 Cascade Engine — Formal Specification
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,931:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Cascade Engine simulates failure propagation through the dependency graph. Its semantics are formally defined
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,948:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: as a Labeled Transition System (LTS), providing provable correctness properties. The LTS formalism is not
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,951:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: optional; it is the defining mechanism of the cascade engine, distinguishing this system from connectivity-based or
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,952:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: heuristic failure models.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,953:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.4.1 Labeled Transition System Definition
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,954:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Cascade Propagation Semantics (CPS) operates over a Labeled Transition System M = (S, S
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,955:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0, Act, ->, F)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: where:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,957:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: State
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,958:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  S = (H, L, T, V) is a 4-tuple:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,959:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Symbol | Domain | Description |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,959:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,960:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |--------|--------|-------------|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,961:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,967:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | H | Component -> HealthStatus | Maps each
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,969:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: component to its health status. HealthStatus = {HEALTHY, DEGRADED, OVERLOADED, DOWN} |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,969:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,972:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | L |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,973:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Component -> R>=0 | Maps each component to its accumulated latency in milliseconds |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,974:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,976:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | T | R>=0 | Global elapsed
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,978:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: time in seconds since fault injection |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,979:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,981:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | V | P(Component) | The set of already-visited components (monotonically
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,982:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: growing) |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,983:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Infrastructure Graph
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,984:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  G = (C, E, dep, w, tau, cb):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,985:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Symbol | Domain | Description |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,986:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,987:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |--------|--------|-------------|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,989:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,990:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | C | Finite set | Set of infrastructure components
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,991:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (vertices) |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,992:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,993:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | E | C x C | Directed dependency edges. (a, b) in E means a depends on b |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,994:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,996:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | dep | E -> {requires,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,998:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: optional, async} | Dependency type function |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,998:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:58,999:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | w | E -> 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,000:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,001:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0, 1
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,001:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,002:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Edge weight (criticality) function |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,003:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,005:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | tau | C -> R>=0 |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,006:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Timeout function: tau(c) is component c
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,006:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,007:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s timeout in milliseconds |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,008:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,010:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | cb | E -> {enabled, disabled} | Circuit breaker
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,011:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: status for each edge |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,012:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Initial State:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,013:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Given a fault injection on component c
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,014:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,015:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0 with fault type f:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,016:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: S_0 = (H_0, L_0, 0, {c_0})
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,018:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: H_0(c) = { apply_direct_effect(c_0, f)   if c = c_0
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,019:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:           { HEALTHY                        otherwise
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,020:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: L_0(c) = { latency_direct(c_0, f)        if c = c_0
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,021:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:           { 0                              otherwise
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,022:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Terminal States:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,030:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A state S = (H, L, T, V) is terminal when: (1) queue exhaustion — no unvisited components are
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,032:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: reachable from any failed component; (2) depth limit — propagation depth reaches D
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,034:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,038:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: max = 20; or (3) circuit breaker
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,040:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: isolation — all remaining paths pass through tripped circuit breakers.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,041:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Actions:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,042:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Act = {inject, propagate, timeout, trip
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,043:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,044:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cb, degrade, terminate}
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,045:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.4.2 Transition Rules
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,058:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The LTS defines eight transition rules that govern cascade behavior. Critically, these rules differentiate propagation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,060:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: based on dependency type — a distinction absent from connectivity-based approaches that treat all edges identically.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,063:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rule 1: Fault Injection (Initial)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,065:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                     H(c_0) = HEALTHY
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,067:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     ---------------------------------------------------------
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,069:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     (H, L, 0, {}) --[inject(c_0, f)]--> (H', L', 0, {c_0})
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,071:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     where H'(c) = { effect(f)  if c = c_0      L'(c) = { lat(f)  if
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,071:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: c = c_0
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,073:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                    { H(c)       otherwise                { 0      
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,073:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: otherwise
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,074:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     effect: FaultType -> HealthStatus
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,075:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     effect(COMPONENT_DOWN)             = DOWN
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     effect(DISK_FULL)                  = DOWN
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     effect(MEMORY_EXHAUSTION)          = DOWN
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,077:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     effect(NETWORK_PARTITION)          = DOWN
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,078:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     effect(CONNECTION_POOL_EXHAUSTION) = DOWN
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     effect(CPU_SATURATION)             = OVERLOADED
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,080:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     effect(TRAFFIC_SPIKE)              = OVERLOADED
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,081:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     effect(LATENCY_SPIKE)              = DEGRADED
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,082:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rule 2: Cascade Propagation (Required Dependency, Single Replica)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     (c', c) in E    dep(c', c) = requires    c' not in V
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     H(c) in {DOWN, OVERLOADED}    replicas(c') = 1    depth < D_max
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:    
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,087:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: -----------------------------------------------------------------
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,090:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     (H, L, T, V) --[propagate(c, c', h')]--> (H[c' |-> h'], L[c'
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,091:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |-> l'], T + dt, V u {c'})
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,092:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     where h' = { DOWN        if H(c) = DOWN
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,094:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                { OVERLOADED  if H(c) = OVERLOADED and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,095:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: utilization(c') > 70%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,097:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                { DEGRADED    if H(c) = OVERLOADED and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,099:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: utilization(c') <= 70%
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,100:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:           l' = { tau(c')                     if h' = DOWN
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,102:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                { edge_latency(c',c) * 3.0    if h' = OVERLOADED
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,104:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                { edge_latency(c',c) * 2.0    if h' = DEGRADED
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,105:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rule 3: Cascade Propagation (Required Dependency, Multiple Replicas)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,107:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     (c', c) in E    dep(c', c) = requires    c' not in V
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,109:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     H(c) = DOWN    replicas(c') > 1    depth < D_max
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,110:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     ---------------------------------------------------
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,114:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     (H, L, T, V) --[degrade(c', "replicas absorb")]--> (H[c' |->
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,116:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DEGRADED], L, T + 5, V u {c'})
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,124:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: When the dependent has multiple replicas, a DOWN dependency causes degradation (not failure), because
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,126:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: remaining replicas absorb the load. Cascade does not continue propagating from c
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,127:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,128:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  in this case.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,129:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rule 4: Optional Dependency
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,131:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     (c', c) in E    dep(c', c) = optional    c' not in V
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,132:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     H(c) = DOWN    depth < D_max
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,133:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     -------------------------------------------------------
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,136:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     (H, L, T, V) --[degrade(c', "optional dep down")]--> (H[c' |->
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,137:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DEGRADED], L, T + 10, V u {c'})
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,138:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rule 5: Async Dependency
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,140:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     (c', c) in E    dep(c', c) = async    c' not in V
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,141:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     H(c) = DOWN    depth < D_max
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,142:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     -------------------------------------------------------
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,147:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     (H, L, T, V) --[degrade(c', "async queue buildup")]--> (H[c'
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,148:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |-> DEGRADED], L, T + 60, V u {c'})
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,149:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rule 6: Circuit Breaker Trip
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,150:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     (c', c) in E    cb(c', c) = enabled    c' not in V
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,151:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     accumulated_latency(c) + edge_latency(c', c) > tau(c')
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,152:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     ---------------------------------------------------------------
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,155:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     (H, L, T, V) --[trip_cb(c, c')]--> (H[c' |-> DEGRADED], L[c'
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,156:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |-> l_acc], T, V u {c'})
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,157:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: When a circuit breaker is enabled and the accumulated latency exceeds the dependent
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,158:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,163:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s timeout, the circuit breaker
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,164:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trips, the dependent is marked DEGRADED, and cascade stops through this path.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,166:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rule 7: Timeout Propagation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,166:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     (c', c) in E    c' not in V
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,167:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     cb(c', c) = disabled
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,168:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     accumulated_latency(c) + edge_latency(c', c) > tau(c')
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,169:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     ---------------------------------------------------------------
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,172:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     (H, L, T, V) --[timeout(c', l_acc)]--> (H[c' |-> DOWN], L[c'
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,173:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |-> l_acc], T, V u {c'})
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,174:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rule 8: Termination
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,175:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     forall c in C \ V : (no applicable rule from Rules 2-7)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,176:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     --------------------------------------------------------
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,178:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     (H, L, T, V) --[terminate]--> (H, L, T, V)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,179:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.4.3 Correctness Properties
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,181:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Theorem 1 (Termination):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,187:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  CPS terminates for all finite infrastructure graphs. Each non-terminal transition strictly
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,188:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: decreases the measure mu(S) = |C 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,189:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,195:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  V|. Since mu(S) >= 0 and mu(S) is a natural number, the sequence of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,199:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: non-terminal transitions is finite. At most |C| non-terminal transitions can occur.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,201:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Theorem 2 (Time Complexity):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,217:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  For acyclic graphs, CPS terminates in O(|C| + |E|) time. Each component is visited
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: at most once, and for each visited component, all dependents are examined. For cyclic graphs with depth limit,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,223:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: termination is guaranteed in O(min(|C|, D
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,224:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,225:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: max) 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,226:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,226:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |E|) steps.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,227:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Theorem 3 (Monotonicity of Failure):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,238:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Once a component transitions to DOWN, it cannot return to HEALTHY,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,242:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DEGRADED, or OVERLOADED within that simulation run. Health can only worsen or stay the same. Formally,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,244:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: for every transition S --
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,244:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,245:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,246:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,247:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: --> S
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,248:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,249:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  and every component c: H
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,250:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,251:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (c) >= H(c) in the partial order HEALTHY 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,251:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: <
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,252:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,253:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DEGRADED 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,253:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: <
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,254:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  OVERLOADED 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,255:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: <
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,256:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  DOWN. This ensures conservative worst-case analysis.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,257:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Theorem 4 (Causality):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,275:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A component can transition from HEALTHY to a degraded state only if at least one of its
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,282:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: dependencies has a non-HEALTHY status. Every failure in the simulation has an explainable causal chain back to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,284:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the injected fault, with no spontaneous failures.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Theorem 5 (Circuit Breaker Correctness):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  If a circuit breaker is enabled on edge (c
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,288:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , c) and accumulated latency
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: exceeds tau(c
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,291:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,292:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ), then: (1) cascade is stopped at c
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,293:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,294:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ; (2) c
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,295:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,296:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  is marked DEGRADED (not DOWN); (3) components
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,297:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: downstream of c
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,298:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,299:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  are not affected by this cascade path.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,301:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Theorem 6 (Dependency Type Attenuation):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,311:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The maximum cascade depth through optional or async dependency
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: edges is 1 (they do not propagate further), because these rules produce DEGRADED status, which does not trigger
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,318:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: recursive propagation.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,320:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Theorem 7 (Blast Radius Bound):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,323:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  For any fault injection, the number of affected components is at most min(|C|,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,325:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: reachable(c
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,326:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,327:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0)) where reachable(c
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,328:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,330:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0) is the set of components transitively reachable from c
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,331:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,332:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0 via reverse
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,333:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: dependency edges.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,334:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.4.4 Direct Effect Computation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,347:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: For each fault f applied to component c, the direct effect is computed based on the fault type as defined in Rule 1.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,349:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The likelihood score (0.2 to 1.0) is computed based on the current state proximity to the failure condition.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,350:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.4.5 Latency Cascade Simulation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,351:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A specialized cascade mode simulates latency propagation through the dependency graph:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,352:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,353:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Accumulated latency is tracked through each hop
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,353:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,354:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Circuit breakers are evaluated at each edge (cascade stopped if latency exceeds timeout)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,355:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,356:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Connection pool exhaustion is computed when accumulated latency causes request pileup
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,357:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,358:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Retry storms are modeled as connection multiplication factors
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,358:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,359:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Singleflight (request coalescing) is modeled as a load reduction factor
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,360:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.4.6 Severity Scoring
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,361:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Cascade severity is computed as:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,362:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: severity = impact_score * spread_score * 10.0 * likelihood
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,363:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,364:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,365:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: impact
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,365:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,366:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: score = (DOWN
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,367:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,367:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: count 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,368:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,369:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1.0 + OVERLOADED
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,370:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,370:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: count 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,371:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,372:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  0.5 + DEGRADED
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,373:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,373:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: count 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,374:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,375:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  0.25)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,376:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: / affected
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,376:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,377:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: count
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,378:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,378:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: spread
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,379:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,380:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: score = affected
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,380:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,381:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: count / total
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,382:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: components
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,384:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Caps: no cascade (single component) -> max 3.0; 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,385:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: <
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,386:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 30% spread -> max 6.0; degraded-only -> max
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,386:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.0
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,387:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.4.7 Validation Against Real Incidents
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,399:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: CPS predictions have been validated against documented cascade failure patterns from real-world incidents. Given
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,402:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the topology and dependency configuration of each incident, CPS predicts the observed cascade path. Validation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,404:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: covers:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,406:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Incident Pattern | CPS Mechanism | Formal Rule |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,407:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,408:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |-----------------|---------------|-------------|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,409:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,411:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Sequential cascade
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,412:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: through single points of failure | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,412:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,414:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: propagate with requires deps, replicas=1 | Rule 2 |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,415:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,416:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Degradation absorption via
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: replicas | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,418:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,419:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: propagate with replicas > 1 | Rule 3 |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,419:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Circuit breaker containment | trip
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,422:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cb in latency cascade | Rule 6 |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,423:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,424:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,425:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Timeout-driven cascade | simulate
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,426:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,427:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: latency
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,427:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,428:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cascade BFS | Rule 7 |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,431:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Traffic redistribution overload | simulate
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,432:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,433:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: traffic
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,433:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,434:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: spike | Rule 1 (OVERLOADED) |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,435:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,437:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Graceful degradation via optional deps | Optional/async dep attenuation | Rules
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,438:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4-5 |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,457:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Backtest against 18 documented public cloud incidents (AWS us-east-1 2021, AWS S3 2017, Meta BGP 2021,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,465:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Cloudflare 2022, GCP 2019, Azure 2023, and others) achieves: Avg Precision 1.000, Avg Recall 1.000, Avg F1
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,468:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Score 1.000, Avg Severity Accuracy 0.819 (with shared infrastructure modeling).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,469:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.5 N-Layer Availability Constraint Model — Formal Specification
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,576:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The N-Layer Availability Constraint Model provides mathematically distinct availability ceilings that constrain
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,646:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cascade simulation results. The core insight is that system availability is bounded by multiple independent factors,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,687:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: each of which imposes a ceiling that cannot be exceeded regardless of improvements in other layers. When a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,708:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cascade simulation predicts an availability exceeding any layer ceiling, the result is flagged as exceeding the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,714:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: computed availability ceiling, and the binding constraint layer — the layer producing the minimum ceiling — is identified
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,715:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: as the target for infrastructure modification.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,717:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Mathematical Formulation:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,720:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: For a system with components C = {c
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,721:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,722:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1, c
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,722:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,723:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2, ..., c
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,723:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,724:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: n} and dependency graph G = (C, E):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,725:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Layer 1 (Hardware Limit):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,726:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: For each component c_i:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,727:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   A_single(c_i) = MTBF(c_i) / (MTBF(c_i) + MTTR(c_i))
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,728:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   A_tier(c_i) = 1 - (1 - A_single(c_i))^replicas(c_i)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,729:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   If failover enabled:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,730:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     fo_events/year = (365.25 * 24 / MTBF(c_i)) * replicas(c_i)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,733:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     fo_downtime_fraction = fo_events * (promotion_time +
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,733:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: detection_time) / (365.25 * 24 * 3600)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,735:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     A_tier(c_i) = A_tier(c_i) * (1 - fo_downtime_fraction)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,736:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A_hw = product{c_i in critical_path(G)} A_tier(c_i)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,737:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where critical
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,738:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,739:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: path(G) includes all components that have at least one requires-type dependent or are leaf nodes.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Layer 2 (Software Limit):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A_sw = min(1 - (deploy_freq * avg_deploy_downtime / period +
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,743:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: human_error_rate + config_drift_rate), A_hw)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,744:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Layer 3 (Theoretical Limit):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,745:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A_theoretical = A_hw * (1 - avg_packet_loss) * (1 -
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,746:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: avg_gc_fraction)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,753:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This is the irreducible physical noise floor from network packet loss rates, garbage collection pause fractions, and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,755:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: kernel scheduling jitter, applied as multiplicative penalties.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,757:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Layer 4 (Operational Limit):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,759:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: effective_response = (mean_response / coverage) * runbook_factor *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,761:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: automation_factor
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,762:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A_ops = 1 - (incidents/year * effective_response / 8760)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,764:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where effective response time is adjusted by on-call coverage percentage, runbook coverage, and automation level.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,765:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Layer 5 (External SLA Cascading):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,768:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A_external = product{c_i in external_deps} SLA(c_i)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,770:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This establishes the hard ceiling imposed by third-party service availability.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,771:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: N-Layer Generalization:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The model is extensible to N layers. Additional layers include but are not limited to: Layer 6 (Geographic Limit) —
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,844:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: availability ceiling imposed by geographic distance and data residency requirements; Layer 7 (Economic Limit) —
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,853:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: availability ceiling imposed by budget constraints where cost increases exponentially per additional nine; Layer N
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,855:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (Custom Domain-Specific Limit) — any domain-specific constraint imposing an independent availability ceiling.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Effective System Availability:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A_system = min(A_layer1, A_layer2, ..., A_layerN)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Binding Constraint Identification:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,859:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: binding_layer = argmin over k (A_layer_k)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,869:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The binding constraint layer is the layer producing the minimum availability ceiling. The system generates an
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,871:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: infrastructure modification specification targeting the binding layer, identifying specific parameter changes (e.g., 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,872:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: increase MTBF of component X from 720h to 2000h
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  or 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: add 2 replicas to component Y
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ) required to relax the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: binding constraint and shift the bottleneck to the next most constraining layer.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,882:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Cascade Path Availability Computation:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,883:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The model integrates with the cascade engine
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,884:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s dependency graph to compute availability along each cascade path.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,888:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: For a cascade path P = 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,888:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,889:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: c
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,889:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,890:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1, c
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,891:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,891:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2, ..., c
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,892:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,892:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: k
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,893:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,893:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  where each c
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: i depends on c
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,896:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {i-1}, the path availability is:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,897:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A_path(P) = product{i=1}^{k} A_tier(c_i) *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,898:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: attenuation(dep_type(c_i, c_{i-1}))
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,900:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where attenuation is 1.0 for requires, 0.3 for optional, and 0.1 for async dependencies.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,901:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Simulation Result Constraining:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,903:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: After the cascade engine computes simulation-predicted availability for each scenario, the N-Layer model constrains
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,903:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the results:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,904:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If A_simulation > A_system:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,905:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Flag result as "exceeding the computed availability ceiling"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,908:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Report: "Simulation predicts {A_simulation} but {binding_layer}
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,909:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: imposes ceiling of {A_system}"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,910:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Generate modification specification for binding_layer
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,912:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This integration ensures that optimistic simulation predictions are bounded by physical reality, preventing
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,913:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: unrealizable availability claims.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,914:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.6 AI Agent Cross-Layer Failure Simulation — Formal Specification
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:42:59,980:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The system extends the infrastructure topology model to include AI-specific component types and failure modes,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,019:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: enabling resilience evaluation of AI agent architectures within the same in-memory simulation framework. This is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,038:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the first system to model infrastructure components and AI agents in a single directed graph, enabling simulation of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,045:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: how infrastructure faults propagate through data availability layers to affect agent behavior, and generating
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,046:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: infrastructure monitoring thresholds from the resulting hallucination probability computations.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,047:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.6.1 AI Component Types
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,048:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Four component types extend the graph model:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,049:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,050:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ai
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,051:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,052:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: agent
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,070:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : An LLM-powered agent that processes requests using tools and makes autonomous
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,080:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: decisions. Modeled as a vertex with attributes for context window size (tokens), supported tool list,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,082:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: fallback policy (degrade/fail/retry), maximum retry count, and base hallucination rate h
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,083:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0(a).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: llm
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,087:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: endpoint
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,092:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : An LLM API endpoint (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google, self-hosted) with rate limit
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,094:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: thresholds, SLA constraints, token-per-minute quotas, and cost-per-token attributes.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,095:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,096:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tool
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,097:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,098:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: service
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,105:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : An external tool or API that agents invoke (database queries, web search, MCP
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,106:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: servers), modeled with availability SLA, response time distribution, and payload size constraints.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,107:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,108:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: agent
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,109:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,110:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: orchestrator
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,119:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : A multi-agent coordination layer supporting sequential, parallel, and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,121:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: hierarchical orchestration patterns, modeled with coordination protocol type, timeout policy, and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,122:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: partial-failure handling strategy.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,124:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.6.2 Hallucination Probability Model H(a, D, I)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,125:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Definition.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,127:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Let H(a, D, I) denote the probability of hallucination for agent a, given:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,128:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,129:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: D = set of data sources available to agent a (grounding databases, retrieval indices, tool outputs)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,130:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,132:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: I = infrastructure state (mapping of each component to {HEALTHY, DEGRADED, DOWN,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,133:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OVERLOADED})
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,134:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Base Hallucination Rate.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,135:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Every agent a has an intrinsic base hallucination rate h
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,136:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,137:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0(a) in 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,137:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,138:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0, 1
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,138:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,139:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , reflecting the model
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,139:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,141:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s inherent tendency to produce ungrounded outputs even when all data sources are available.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,141:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Data Source Dependency Weights.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,142:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  For each data source d in D(a), w(d) in 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,144:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,144:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0, 1
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,145:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,146:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  defines how critical data source d
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,147:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: is to agent a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,148:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,148:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s grounding.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,149:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Per-Source Hallucination Contribution.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,150:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  For each data source d:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,150:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If status(d, I) = HEALTHY:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,153:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     h_d = h_0(a)                                          (no
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,154:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: additional risk)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,154:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If status(d, I) = DOWN:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,156:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     h_d = h_0(a) + (1 - h_0(a)) * w(d)                    (full
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,156:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: dependency risk)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,157:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If status(d, I) = DEGRADED:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,160:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     h_d = h_0(a) + (1 - h_0(a)) * w(d) * delta            (partial
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,161:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: risk)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,162:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     where delta in (0, 1) is the degradation factor (default: 0.5)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,163:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If status(d, I) = OVERLOADED:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,164:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     h_d = h_0(a) + (1 - h_0(a)) * w(d) * omega            
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,165:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (overload risk)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,166:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     where omega in (0, 1) is the overload factor (default: 0.3)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,167:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This formula ensures: when h
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,167:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,168:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0 = 0 and w(d) = 1, h
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,168:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,170:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d = 1 (total hallucination when fully dependent source is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: down); when h
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,172:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0 = 1, h
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,173:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,173:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d = 1 regardless (already hallucinating); h
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,174:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,175:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d is always in 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,175:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,176:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: h
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,177:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,177:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0(a), 1
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,178:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,179:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: .
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,180:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Combined Hallucination Probability (independence assumption):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,181:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: H(a, D, I) = 1 - product{d in D(a), status(d,I) != HEALTHY} (1 -
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,182:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: h_d)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,183:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: When all data sources are HEALTHY: H(a, D, I) = h
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,183:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,184:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0(a). When no data sources exist: H(a, D, I) = h
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,185:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,185:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0(a).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,187:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Properties:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,189:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (1) Monotonicity — H increases as more data sources fail; (2) Boundedness — H(a, D, I) in 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,190:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,191:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: h
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,192:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,192:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 0(a), 1
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,193:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,201:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ; (3)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,206:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Compositionality — each data source contributes independently; (4) Infrastructure-dependent — H is a function of I, linking
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,208:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: agent behavior to infrastructure state.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,210:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.6.3 Cross-Layer Cascade Model
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,212:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The system defines four layers of cross-layer cascade:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,213:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Layer | Name | Domain |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,213:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,214:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |-------|------|--------|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,216:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | L1 | Infrastructure | Physical/virtual component failures |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,217:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,218:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | L2 | Data
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,219:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Availability | Grounding source accessibility |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,220:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,221:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | L3 | Agent Behavior | AI-specific failure modes |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,221:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,223:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | L4 | Downstream
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,224:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Impact | Propagation to consumers |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,225:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Formal Transition Model:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,227:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: L1: Infrastructure fault F occurs on component c
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,227:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,229:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     For each data source d reachable from c in dependency graph G:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,230:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         status(d, I) transitions from HEALTHY to {DEGRADED, DOWN,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,231:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OVERLOADED}
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,232:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: L2: Data source d becomes unavailable/degraded
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,233:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,234:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     For each agent a where d in D(a):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,235:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         H(a, D, I) is recomputed using updated status(d, I)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,236:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         If H(a, D, I) > threshold_hallucination:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,237:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             agent a enters DEGRADED state (hallucination mode)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,238:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: L3: Agent a produces unreliable output
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,239:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,240:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     For each downstream consumer b that receives output from a:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,241:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         If b is an agent:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,242:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             b's effective input quality degrades
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,243:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             H(b, D', I) increases (tainted input acts as degraded
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,244:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: data source)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,245:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         If b is a system/user:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,245:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             Impact propagates as corrupted data
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,246:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: L4: Compound cascade
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,247:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,248:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     Agent-to-agent propagation follows the same graph traversal
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,250:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     as infrastructure cascades, but in the agent dependency
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,250:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: subgraph
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,251:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.6.4 Agent Failure Taxonomy (10 Modes)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,252:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | ID | Failure Mode | Health Impact | Trigger |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,253:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,254:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |----|-------------|---------------|---------|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,255:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,264:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | hallucination | Confident but
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,266:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: incorrect output not grounded in data | DEGRADED | Data source dependency severed; H(a,D,I) > threshold |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,267:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,268:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,269:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: context
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,270:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,274:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: overflow | Input exceeds token limit | DOWN | Cumulative tokens > max
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,281:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: context
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,283:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tokens |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,288:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | token
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,289:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,299:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: exhaustion | API budget depleted | DOWN | consumed
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,301:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,303:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tokens >= budget
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,304:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,305:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tokens |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,306:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,308:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | prompt
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,309:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,320:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: injection | Adversarial
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,322:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: input hijacks behavior | DEGRADED | Unsanitized external input with directive text |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,323:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,325:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | agent
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,326:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,329:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: loop | Infinite tool call
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,330:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cycles without progress | DOWN | tool
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,331:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,332:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: calls > max
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,334:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,336:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: iterations without progress |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,338:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,339:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | confidence
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,340:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,344:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: miscalibration | High
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,346:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: confidence on incorrect outputs | DEGRADED | Distribution shift; degraded grounding |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,347:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,347:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | cot
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,348:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,352:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: collapse | Reasoning
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,353:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: degrades mid-generation | DEGRADED | Token budget pressure; context saturation |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,354:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,354:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | output
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,355:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,361:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: amplification |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,364:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Hallucination consumed by downstream agent | DEGRADED to DOWN | Agent-to-agent flow without validation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,364:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: gates |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,365:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,366:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | grounding
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,367:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,369:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: staleness | Data sources available but outdated | DEGRADED | Cache TTL expiry; replication
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,369:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: lag |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,370:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,371:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | llm
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,372:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,372:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: rate
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,373:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,375:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: limit | API throttling causes timeout cascade | OVERLOADED | Traffic spike; concurrent
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,376:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: invocations |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,378:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Each failure mode is formally defined with conditions for triggering, health impact on the agent vertex, and recovery
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,379:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: characteristics.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,380:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.6.5 Agent-to-Agent Cascade Propagation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,382:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: When agents form a directed acyclic graph (DAG) of data flow, a failure in one agent propagates through the graph:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Given agent graph G_agent = (A, E) where:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,384:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     A = set of agents
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,386:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     E = set of directed edges (a_i -> a_j) meaning a_j consumes
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,387:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: output of a_i
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,388:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: For a source agent a_s with hallucination probability H(a_s):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,389:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     For each edge (a_s -> a_t) in E:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         amplification_factor(a_s, a_t) = 1.0 if a_t has no
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: independent verification
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:                                        = v(a_t) in [0, 1) if a_t
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: can partially verify
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,396:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         H_effective(a_t) = 1 - (1 - H(a_t, D, I)) * (1 - H(a_s) *
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,397:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: amplification_factor(a_s, a_t))
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,398:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Compound Cascade Probability
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,400:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  for a chain of agents 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,400:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,401:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,402:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,403:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1, a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,405:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,406:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2, ..., a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,407:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,408:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: n
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,408:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,409:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: :
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,411:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: H_chain(a_n) = 1 - product{i=1}^{n} (1 - H_effective(a_i))
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,412:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Properties:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,413:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (1) Amplification — H
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,414:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,415:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: chain(a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,416:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: n) >= max(H(a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,423:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: i)) for all i; (2) Monotonic growth — adding agents never
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,425:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: decreases compound risk; (3) Mitigation — validation gates between agents reduce amplification
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,426:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,427:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: factor, bounding
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,428:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cascade growth.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,430:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.6.6 Infrastructure Monitoring Threshold Generation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,437:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The system derives infrastructure monitoring thresholds from the hallucination probability model. For each AI agent
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,438:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: a with a configured maximum acceptable hallucination probability H
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,439:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,443:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: max(a), the system computes the minimum
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,444:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: data source health required to maintain H(a, D, I) 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,445:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: <
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: = H
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,447:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: max(a):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: For each data source d in D(a):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,449:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     threshold_health(d, a) = minimum health state of d such that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,451:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         H(a, D, I) <= H_max(a) given current state of all other
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,452:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: data sources
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,453:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     monitoring_alert(d, a) = {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,455:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         trigger: status(d, I) degradation approaching
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,456:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: threshold_health(d, a),
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,457:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         severity: proportional to w(d) * (H_max(a) - h_0(a)),
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,460:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         action: "Data source {d} health degradation threatens agent
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,461:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {a} hallucination threshold"
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,462:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     }
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,485:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: These monitoring thresholds bridge the gap between infrastructure monitoring (which tracks component health) and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,493:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: AI agent reliability (which depends on grounding data availability), providing concrete, actionable alerts that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,496:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: infrastructure operators can use to prevent agent behavioral degradation before it occurs.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,497:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.6.7 Grounding Data Dependency Tracking
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,498:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The system maintains a dependency map from each ai
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,499:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,500:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: agent vertex to its grounding data sources (tool
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,501:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,508:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: service
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,511:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vertices providing database queries, retrieval indices, web search results). When the cascade engine processes a fault
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,513:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: that affects any tool
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,514:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,515:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: service vertex, the system:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,516:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,517:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Identifies all ai
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,518:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,519:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: agent vertices that depend on the affected tool
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,520:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,521:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: service
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,521:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,523:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Recomputes H(a, D, I) for each affected agent using the updated infrastructure state
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,523:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,525:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If H(a, D, I) exceeds the configured hallucination threshold, transitions the agent to DEGRADED
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,526:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: state
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,526:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,528:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Propagates the degradation through the agent dependency subgraph using the compound cascade
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,529:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: probability model
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,530:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.6.8 Tool Call Loop Detection
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,532:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The system detects tool call loops by monitoring simulated request patterns on ai
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,532:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,534:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: agent vertices. A loop is detected
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,535:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: when: (1) the agent
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,536:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,537:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s simulated request count exceeds max
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,537:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,562:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: iterations within a time window; (2) no state progression
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,578:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: is detected (the agent is not making progress toward task completion); (3) the same tool is being invoked repeatedly
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,584:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: with similar parameters. Upon detection, the agent vertex transitions to DOWN state and cascade propagation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,585:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: continues to its dependents.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,586:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.7 Additional Simulation Engines (Summary)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,594:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The system provides over one hundred complementary simulation and analysis engines beyond the core cascade,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-22 12:43:00,596:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: availability, and AI agent engines. The following table summarizes key engines by category:
